data.title: Alec Douglas-Home Signed Oversized Photograph
data.meta_description: Sold for $250 | Prime Minister of the United Kingdom (1903-1995) who served from 1963 to 1964. He was the only British prime minister born during the Edwardian
data.text:
Description

Prime Minister of the United Kingdom (1903-1995) who served from 1963 to 1964. He was the only British prime minister born during the Edwardian era, and the last to hold office while a member of the House of Lords, before disclaiming his peerage and taking up a seat in the House of Commons for the remainder of his premiership. Uncommon vintage matte-finish photo of the former British prime minister by Vivienne of London, affixed to the original 10.25 x 13.5 mount, which is signed in ballpoint, "Alec Douglas-Home, 1965." In very good to fine condition, with several stains to the image.
